cs.GT, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.HC 

The paper deals with game-theoretic design of a rating protocol to stimulate cooperation among self-interested users in crowdsourcing. This involves analyzing the behavior of a large number of anonymous users having asymmetric service requirements, different service capabilities, and dynamically joining/leaving a crowdsourcing platform with imperfect monitoring. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.GT (Computer Science > Game Theory)
- cs.CY (Computer Science > Cryptography and Security)
- cs.SI (Computer Science > Social and Information Networks)
- cs.DS (Computer Science > Data Structures and Algorithms)
- cs.HC (Computer Science > Human-Computer Interaction)
